Chuck, SPAN is already MX'd.  Since SPAN is clearly a NASA network,
we created a span.nasa.gov subdomain is supported by some local
DECNET-INTERNET mail relays.  Instead of user@host.span (ugly, and
locally dependent), try user@host.span.nasa.gov.  That will get
you 2 MX records, and both systems will do a fine job of providing
relay services.  

BITNET is much harder to pin down, as it doesn't really fit into
anyone's 2nd level domain...

					Thanks,
					   Milo

